What is this?
-------------

Niepce Digital is a digital photography software.

It is currently work in progress.

To build is you need the following:
-----------------------------------

A C++ compiler
gtk+ 3.2
cairo 1.1
gtkmm 3.2
giomm
cairomm
sqlite3
libxml2 > 2.5.0
boost 1.34
 -boost test (for the unit test)
exempi >= 2.2.0
libopenraw >= 0.0.5
geglmm >= 0.1.0
gegl >= 0.1.0
babl
libgphoto2

Niepce is being developped on Linux. It should build and work on other
UNIX systems.


Working on Debian
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
In order to get Niepce working on Debian you should have to install:
aptitude install \
> libexempi-dev libopenraw-dev libopenrawgnome-dev libgtkmm-3-dev 

Debian (nor Ubuntu) do not still pack geglmm. In order to get it visit 
to get the latest version:
http://ftp.gnome.org/pub/gnome/sources/geglmm/

Working on SUSE
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

[ there used to be stuff in the openSUSE build service ]

